SIMPLE: protrude
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Protrude
<hw>Pro*trude"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Protruded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Protruding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>protrudere</ets>,
<ets>protrusum</ets>; <ets>pro</ets> forward + <ets>trudere</ets> to
thrust. See <er>Threat</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To thrust forward; to drive or force along.</def>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To thrust out, as through a narrow orifice or from
confinement; to cause to come forth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When . . . Spring <qex>protrudes</qex> the bursting gems.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protrude</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Protrude
<hw>Pro*trude"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To shoot out or forth; to be
thrust forward; to extend beyond a limit; to project.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The parts <qex>protrude</qex> beyond the skin.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protrusile</ent>⟦br⟧
